                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. I received him in charge - he said he was distressed.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was walking by the shop - a young man tapped me on the shoulder, and asked me to carry the parcel for him - and told me to put it in my apron; there was a cry of Stop thief! he ran, and I ran too - but lost him.</p>

